 of the labour movement from the Second World War to today. Providing an insider's perspective on union developments and issues, One Day Longer is a profound reflection of Williams's impressive career.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269925040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442699250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442699250.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK